    "en": {
      "title": "QR system reduces import cost",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Power and Energy has informed that the implementation of QR system has reduced the monthly cost of fuel import.",
        "The ministry noted that the monthly cost of fuel import has decreased from 500 million dollars to 230 million dollars.",
        "Apart from providing quota-based fuel distribution scheme to people in Sri Lanka, the QR system has also led to national savings, the ministry said.",
        "With more than six million vehicles currently registered for the National Fuel Licence, 93% of fuel stations across the country use the QR system, the ministry said."
      ],
